Acmqueue iOS app restore subscription issue
text:
Both on iPhone or iPad I am unable to restore my purchase subscription in acmqueue app. I am getting forever the acmqueue white logo on a green background.

I do not know whether it is related to iOS 16 or if the issue existed before.

I have tried to uninstall the app, then reinstall it but no luck: the only thing is that I have lost access to all previously downloaded issues.

Does anyone have the same problem? If yes then what is your iOS version?

GitHub Banned Me Permanently
text:
A few months ago, I’ve made some controversial comments on an open source project discussion that I regret. Because of these comments, GitHub decided to permanently ban me from the platform.

I can no longer have any account on GitHub, new accounts that I create are hunted and suspended.

I tried appealing the ban, and months have passed with no response from support.

This means that GitHub has effectively suspended my ability to participate in the development community, and also I cannot work as well, because my company uses GitHub, and as soon as GitHub finds out that a account is used by me, the account is immediately banned under the justification that it is being used to sidestep a decision.

I don’t know what to do anymore, I’m afraid, I’m going to be fired if I can’t work, what I’m going to do?

Broken Incentives
Anyone else struggling to get a Software dev job rn?
text:
Recently interviewed with a medium sized company for a backend dev position.

They said I passed the interviews and promised an offer. After a month of "trying to find a customer to place me", telling me I'm a fantastic candidate etc. they finally decided to cancel the verbal offer until maybe next year.

I've recently had other bad experiences were they basically try to find excuses to cut me on interviews. It's like I'm answering the questions correctly minus one, so I'm disqualified.

I don't remember job searching being that hard even a few years ago, anybody relates?

Tell HN: Help defeat poorly implemented dark modes
text:
I've noticed recently that at least two major open source projects have gone to dark mode by default:

https://www.postgresql.org/docs/ and https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.1/

Looks pretty bad - especially the Postgres one. Or am I the only one?

I just want to create awareness among programmers to please stop doing this.

text:
